##85% of small and medium-sized enterprises to survive three months of cash, save his own efforts to deal with the epidemic test

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

"CAIJING" reporters interviewed a number of VC executives said that the cash flow management of small and medium-sized enterprises is crucial, if the cash flow dried up, it is difficult for enterprises to escape the fate of bankruptcy. At present, it is helping the invested enterprises to solve the cash flow problem in various ways

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Yang Xiuhong, Wang Yinglu Ling, Zhang Xinpei, Caijing

Editor | Ling Lu

Lay off the staff, close down, or try to survive in any way you can? The 2020 new crown pneumonia epidemic, the capital chain is already fragile small and medium-sized enterprises, encounter a big test.

In the year of the Gengzi rat, the epidemic was rampant. Many businesses have not been able to escape the economic burden of the epidemic. Since February alone, a number of small and medium-sized enterprises, including the king of Karaoke, brothers, Ming Xi big language and so on, have declared bankruptcy. Wang Jiashu, founder of Mingxi Da Language and literature, explained the reasons behind the company's closure: In the latest financing, investors gave up their investment because of the epidemic.

An online education agency at the forefront of the storm, its financing is still difficult, other small and medium-sized enterprises will encounter what kind of difficulties?

Recently, "finance and Economics" reporter interviewed several small and medium-sized enterprises and more than a dozen investment agencies. According to the reporter from Caijing, at present, most of these VC institutions have held emergency meetings around the Spring Festival, communicating with dozens or even hundreds of companies invested by the companies to discuss how to deal with the impact of this rare epidemic on enterprises, some VC companies are helping individual companies to solve the business of life and death situation.

"One of the business travel companies we invested in has already returned one hundred thousand tickets unconditionally to customers after international and domestic flights were suspended due to the outbreak. During the Spring Festival holiday alone, the company's business refunds amounted to 600 million to 700 million yuan." Chunguangli industrial capital group founder Yang Shoubin told the "financial" reporter said.

Some VC institutions have started to help the funded enterprises to implement the financing problem. On February 13, Wu Haiyan, a partner at Huachuang capital management, wore a face mask and went to the gate of the residential area to receive a city-wide express delivery. He signed several agreements for the change of industry and Commerce, this will complete the necessary formalities for a new investment in the legal process from the end of last year, before the actual delivery.

On February 12, the China Investment Association's Venture Capital Committee (CCVC) released an investigation report on the impact of the epidemic on venture capital firms and their investment enterprises, nearly 90% of the respondents believe that the epidemic has a great or certain impact on the venture capital industry. The sectors most affected by the outbreak include consumer products and services, particularly offline consumer retail, catering and services; logistics and transportation; and culture and entertainment media, particularly film and Television Manufacturing, especially in labor-intensive industries.

Recently, with the number of new cases in non-hubei areas dropped to single digits, the resumption of domestic enterprises to resume production has been put on the agenda, but the overall resumption rate is still worrying. February 25, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology Survey data show that the country's small and medium-sized enterprises resume work rate is currently only about 30% .

How to deal with the impact of this outbreak? "CAIJING" reporters interviewed a number of VC executives said that the cash flow management of small and medium-sized enterprises is crucial, if the cash flow dried up, it is difficult for enterprises to escape the fate of bankruptcy. Is currently helping invested enterprises to solve the cash flow problem. The management of cash flow needs to start from hemostasis, hematopoiesis and blood transfusion.

With regard to hemostasis and Hematopoiesis, a number of VC executives interviewed by Caijing provided a number of suggestions for the companies they invest in, including cutting off businesses that consume too much capital flow, negotiating with employees to slow down payment and reducing pay, the Related Price Difference Company uses the corresponding option to compensate, lets the invested enterprise help each other in the business and so on.

For blood transfusion, a number of VC executives said that the current government support measures for small and medium-sized enterprises, "far water is difficult to quench thirst, " many measures are difficult to actually fall. They have made suggestions to the government, such as setting up special support funds in some cities that can afford them, allowing banks to set up green channels to grant loans to small and medium-sized enterprises as soon as possible, and changing corporate social security from deferred payment to non-payment.

After the outbreak of the investment market, a number of VC executives believe that the economic winter and rare epidemic of the dual impact of surviving enterprises, will be more investment value. At present, some VC companies to invest in the online and fresh field of enterprises, business ushered in explosive growth, fresh enterprises have doubled the monthly business volume. The question then, however, is how these companies can continue to retain new customers after the epidemic.

Liu Zehui, founding partner of Xingtuo capital, told a reporter from CAIJING, "The epidemic will force traditional enterprises to innovate themselves, and some companies with weak management and no ability to operate digitally will have to sell out. Many companies are expected to invest more in digital construction and supply chains in the future. "

"disasters do not necessarily produce great enterprises, but some enterprises will be great because of disasters, " Yang said.

STATUS: 90% of smes may be affected

On February 10th, the first day of work after the Lunar New Year holiday, at the company's staff conference, Zhang Jixue, CEO of trendy media, announced 500 job cuts, or 10% of the total number of employees, and a 20% pay cut for top executives.

"I led my team to overcome SARS in 2003 and the earthquake in 2008, but I was afraid of losing to the new title in 2020 because there was no one on the street and no consumers, which was a bit scary, " Zhang said in an internal speech that day, "although there is still nearly 1 billion yuan in cash on the new wave account, if the revenue goes to zero, it will only last six or seven months. "

The new wave announcement came shortly after the King of Karaoke in Beijing issued an internal letter declaring the company bankrupt and employment contract all employees.

At about the same time, Li Chao, the founder of the company, published a letter to all students, employees and shareholders of the company, saying that as a result of the outbreak, the Beijing campus of the company has stopped recruiting students and all employees have been laid off.

Li Qi, who runs a restaurant in Sanya, told Caijing that the annual profit is almost entirely due to the Chinese New Year. "We basically break even for most of the year, and we won't make a profit for a year until the Lunar New Year. We closed down for the second day of the second year. We lost more than 2 million yuan. We don't plan to do it again. "

"every day I think about how to keep the company, how to keep 300 employees, " Zhang Liang, an executive at a fitness chain, told Caijing, "We are facing a two-to three-month trough. Three months of basic loss of wages, more than 10 million yuan, rent, water, electricity and equipment consumption, close to 6 million yuan, which basically equals the company's full-year profits. "

In accordance with the Ministry of Culture and tourism requirements, after January 27, including outbound teams, all group tours, air tickets and hotel services are suspended. Tour guides, whose main income is commission, are also paid a minimum wage. Ginger, a tour guide, told Caijing that many tour guides don't have a base salary, and a base salary is only the minimum wage, and insurance is paid by themselves, so they can't support the normal operation of their families.

Even those on the cutting edge of online education, some will not survive the winter. In mid-february, Mingxi Dayu, an online education agency once hailed as the dark horse of the big Chinese track, announced the end of its operations. Wang Jiashu, the company's founder, explains why: In the latest round of financing, investors gave up because of the epidemic.

Under the epidemic, there are 1 billion yuan of cash on the account of the enterprise had to cut jobs to save themselves, in the financing of the enterprise declared bankruptcy, more capital shortage of small and medium-sized enterprises status?

Recently, Tsinghua University School of Economics and Management and Peking University HSBC business school jointly surveyed 995 small and medium-sized enterprises, covering catering, retail and other industries. According to the data, 34 percent of the companies had only one month to live with cash on their books, 33.1 percent had two months, and 17.91 percent had three months. That means 85% of companies have a balance of only three months at most.

"CAIJING" reporter recently interviewed a number of VC executives said that the new crown pneumonia epidemic on the invested enterprises can not be ignored. Most of the companies they have invested in have gone online since the start of work day on February 10, but there is still a big gap between them and normal operations. Affected by the epidemic, part of the invested enterprises suffered heavy losses, there are some enterprises upstream, such as fresh e-commerce and internet-related enterprises.

"taken as a whole, there is no doubt that the impact of the epidemic is very broad. Perhaps 90% of businesses will face operational pressure because of the epidemic, the remaining 10% of businesses, because of the epidemic will bring counter-trend growth in business. Some companies may face significant business losses, such as offline-only businesses, vacation apartments that are banned by the state, and businesses with insufficient cash flow,"according to recent analysis and Statistics by the company team, as well as communications with the invested companies, yang shoubin summed up for CAIJING.

"At present, some small and medium-sized enterprises are facing many difficulties in their operations, such as capacity problems, upstream factories not being opened, raw materials not being supplied, customers suspending or suspending their bids, " Peng Cheng, vice president of the Angel Fund, told Caijing.

Wu Haiyan also told Caijing that, "Some Saas companies for msmes whose customers are impacted by the epidemic and cash flow is tight will naturally delay or reduce system procurement inputs, which in turn will affect the operating cash flow of these Saas companies. "

In order to understand the situation of small and medium-sized enterprises and investment institutions under the epidemic, China's venture capital committee recently conducted a random sample survey of nearly 200 venture capital institutions. The survey results show that nearly 90% of the respondents believe that the epidemic has a great impact on the venture capital industry or have a certain impact. More than 95% of the respondents said that the epidemic had had a negative impact on the projects put in, of which 23.35% thought it had a significant impact and 61.93% thought it had a certain impact. In addition, more than 70% of venture capital enterprises and Angel Investors believe that the epidemic will have a serious impact or greater impact on "double creation" (mass entrepreneurship, mass innovation) .

An investigation into the delay is even more grim. According to a recent survey of enterprise capacity led by the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences, about 96 percent of businesses are unable to afford more than a two month delay because of the epidemic. About 67.7 percent of the companies surveyed said they could afford a delay of up to two weeks, about one-fifth could afford a delay of two weeks to one month, and 7.1 percent could afford a delay of more than one month, only 1.7 per cent were able to afford extensions of more than two months.

At the end of February, although the number of new cases in non-hubei areas dropped to single digits, the situation of enterprises returning to work and production is still not optimistic. On February 25, Shu Chaohui, a second-level inspector in the Department of Industrial Policy and regulation of the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology, said that conditions for small and medium-sized enterprises, especially small and micro enterprises, such as production, office conditions, capital and personnel, are relatively weak, and are deeply affected by the epidemic, making it a difficult point for them to resume work and production, that's the point, too. "The Ministry of Industry and Information Technology monitors 2.4 million small and medium-sized enterprises using cloud and e-commerce platforms, and the resumption rate for small and medium-sized enterprises across the country is only about 30 per cent. "

Tian Yulong, chief engineer of the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology, said that at present, small and medium-sized enterprises are mainly faced with "five difficulties" , including difficulties in resuming work, employment, industrial chain matching, financial support, order delivery and so on.

However, quite a number of business owners told the CAIJING reporter that the pre-approval period for resuming work was very strict. Later, as the epidemic eased, the approval period became relatively relaxed, and the more economically developed regions, such as Zhejiang and Jiangsu, the more can be based on market feedback, timely dynamic adjustment. "At first it was a template of seven documents to fill in and submit an application, and it was reviewed at a level and a level. Now it's just a matter of submitting an application and you can resume work on your own. " Some Hangzhou enterprises lamented that the approval efficiency was also higher, "We submitted our application for resumption of work on the 14th and it was approved on the 17th. "

Fast aid: Far Water Can Not Quench near thirst

In the "darkest hour" of small and medium-sized enterprises, from the central to local, a series of rescue policies and measures were quickly introduced.

On February 1, the Central Bank, the Ministry of Finance, the China Banking Regulatory Commission and other five departments jointly issued a paper, issued to strengthen financial support for the epidemic prevention and control of 30 measures. Among them, it is clearly pointed out that enterprises, especially small and micro-enterprises, that are affected by the epidemic, such as wholesale, retail, accommodation, catering and other industries, and those that have the prospect of development but are temporarily affected by the epidemic, shall not blindly draw on, cut off or suppress loans.

On February 2, Suzhou led the way with its "ten policy proposals to support small and medium-sized enterprises in overcoming difficulties" . Ten suggestions are put forward to ensure that the credit balance of small and micro enterprises does not decline, to implement the policy of supporting enterprises and stabilizing posts, and to hold over payment of social insurance premiums. It is understood that the implementation period of the policy is tentatively set at three months from the date the policy is issued. Subsequently, Beijing, Shanghai, Qingdao and other places quickly launched a similar active policy.

Before this, already had a lot of large-scale enterprises to issue a measure one after another actively, support small and medium-sized enterprise. On January 28, Wanda announced a 36-day rent and property free policy for 323 shopping centers across the country from January 25 to February 29. Longhu District, China resources, Poly Property and other property developers have followed. According to incomplete statistics, there are currently nearly 500 Department Store Shopping Center Rent Reduction Initiative.

On February 20, at the State Council's Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism press conference, the Ministry of Human and Social Affairs, the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Housing and Construction and other departments introduced the policy situation of reducing or exempting enterprises from social insurance premiums, medical insurance premiums and holding over-payment of housing accumulation funds, it is expected to exceed 500 billion yuan.

On February 25th the China State Council Executive Meeting said it would defer the payment of interest on loans to eligible msmes, including individual businesses, that are experiencing temporary liquidity difficulties, until June 30th, with no penalty. At the same time, it said it would increase the amount of reloans and rediscount by 500 billion yuan, mainly for small and medium-sized banks to increase credit support for micro, small and medium-sized enterprises.

In the eyes of many small and medium-sized business owners and investors, the scale and speed of the bail-out is unprecedented in history. But also because the new deal out of a shorter time, more hasty, the real implementation of the implementation of the enterprise to take time. A number of VC executives said, I'm afraid far water is difficult to quench near thirst.

"The government has put in place a series of credit and fiscal policies to support smes, but the time frame will not be immediately obvious. Some of the policies are not very realistic either, such as reducing or waiving rent, unless they are part of the operation of the relevant government departments, and other landlords themselves are a problem,"Liu said in an interview with Caijing.

In the view of Mao Daqing, the founder of Youke Factory, deferral, tax relief on the difficulties faced by enterprises today has no direct effect. Although the delay of "five insurance and one gold" can produce some effect on labor-intensive enterprises, the local government has yet to implement it.

Huang Yiping, deputy director of the National Development Research Institute at Peking University, wrote that the Central Bank and regulatory authorities should favor online banks or city firms. "But with the Central Bank's recent 300bn-yuan special refinancing loan, Ōzu has gone to the national commercial banks, which may not be easy to get into the hands of small and medium-sized enterprises. "

How can a series of support policies for smes be implemented?

In Yang's view, some policies need to be improved in terms of accuracy, timeliness and inclusiveness. He made a number of proposals, such as the establishment of special support funds in some cities in a position to do so; the establishment of green channels for banks to grant loans to small and medium-sized enterprises as soon as possible; and the government, according to the actual situation of enterprises, to change their social security deferral to non-payment.

In terms of concrete operation, Yang Shoubin suggested, first, setting up a port for quick loan applications, such as concentrating several large banks, forming an agreed loan interest rate for enterprises in the epidemic, establishing an online approval mechanism, and meeting what specific conditions, businesses can get loans. "The situation is that the policy is not binding on the banks, relying on the banks' self-consciousness, which banks are willing to do, do not want to do it. "

Wu Haiyan, a partner at Huachuang capital management, has a similar suggestion. "The majority of msmes do not have mortgaged fixed assets. Can Financial Institutions comprehensively assess the loan repayment ability of msmes and extend credit based on business data, accounts receivable, etc. in their online systems. "We hope that banks and other financial institutions will improve their assessment of msmes so that they can get loans as soon as possible. "

Second, the social security will be delayed and exempt from the combination. At present, many local governments have introduced the policy of deferring payment of social insurance. In fact, enterprises should be exempted from payment of social insurance for two to three months by combining deferring payment with exemption from payment, taking into account their own conditions. "Don't wait for the company to lose its vital signs before you try to save it. ".

Third, cities in a position to do so will set up special epidemic funds, which will come from the government's guidance fund. Some cities will have a fund of twenty billion RMB, which can be temporarily set aside two billion RMB for specific support. The government can select some potential enterprises to carry out targeted assistance and investment.

"In fact, the most important thing is to maintain the stability, predictability and transparency of the basic policies in various sectors, and to significantly reduce the economic losses suffered by private enterprises in various sectors as a result of over-regulation by the relevant authorities and short-term changes, and to provide them with time and an environment in which they can rest and recuperate, " said Wang Ran, founder of Yikai capital.

Self help: a variety of ways to live

Since "far water is difficult to quench near thirst" , in the face of an unprecedented epidemic, how can this huge group of small and medium-sized enterprises help themselves?

"CAIJING" reporters interviewed a number of VC executives said that is working together to help the investment enterprises to tide over the difficulties. Several executives stressed that money was at the heart of the problem. Once the cash flow dried up, small and medium-sized enterprises will face the risk of failure.

Previously, Jia Guolong, chairman of the well-known domestic food and beverage brand Xibei, had said that the company was in a hurry, losing 780 million yuan during the Spring Festival, and its employees were spending more than 150 million yuan a month on wages, which might not last more than three months. Many small and medium-sized enterprises also said on micro-blogs, Wechat and other platforms that the epidemic has caused difficulties in business operations, if the delay can not start, rely on their own funds, it is difficult to survive for three months.

The aforementioned online education agency, Ming Xi, has gone out of business due to financial difficulties.

"Cash flow is like the blood of a business. In the current epidemic, what we need to consider is whether to survive by self-hematopoiesis or external blood transfusion? I think to maintain cash flow, we need to stop bleeding, hematopoiesis and blood transfusion, " Yang said.

In hemostasis and Hematopoiesis,"CAIJING"reporter interviewed a number of VC executives also gave a more convergent advice. In their view, cash is king at the moment. As for the measures to stop the bleeding, first, the enterprise may consider whether it can cut down the business that consumes more cash flow; second, the enterprise coordinates upstream and downstream, changing the payable amount to deferred payment, etc. . Third, whether can negotiate with the employee to defer the salary, reduce the salary. These methods can help enterprises to reduce the operating cash flow cost in the short term.

On the other hand, VC institutions also recommended that the invested enterprises, so that the non-landed financing as soon as possible, such as the epidemic before some project financing has been negotiated, but still go through the process, it is recommended that it be implemented as soon as possible.

In terms of hematopoiesis, several VC executives said that each enterprise is different and needs to find income-generating conditions according to its own situation, such as offline to online, such as encouraging offline catering enterprises to open up online sales channels, help a number of offline sales enterprises to live platform sales.

There are also VC institutions that coordinate the mutual assistance of the invested enterprises. Yang Shoubin's Chunguangli capital recently launched a Chunguangzhan "epidemic" community, so that the invested enterprises, Chunguangli enterprises and cooperation between Chunguangli effective docking resources and technology, help each other.

Wu Haiyan suggested that these smes and upstream and downstream enterprises to coordinate more in the entire industrial chain to tide over the difficulties.

Liu Zehui suggested that small and medium-sized enterprises open source and reduce costs, self-innovation. "We advise companies to pay attention to controlling costs and cutting unnecessary expenses. Marketing expenses and other expenses that can not produce current income should be controlled. Cost Control for employees is a must, if necessary. The number one has to lead by example and ride out the storm with everyone."

"In this outbreak, some companies with weak digital capabilities have been hurt more. After the estimated epidemic, some do not have the online operation ability, the management is weak the company may have to clear a batch. The epidemic will force traditional businesses to reinvent themselves, and many companies are expected to spend more on digital infrastructure and supply chains in the future. This will improve the operating efficiency of the whole society and change the competitive pattern of the industry,"Liu said.

Liu Erhai, founder and managing partner of pleasant capital, believes that whether the company can innovate itself will affect its ability to withstand the impact of the epidemic. "labour-intensive companies have clearly been hit harder by the epidemic than high-tech companies, so if you don't have a lot of innovation and you're not very efficient, it's dangerous if you have a problem. "

He thinks, although be invested enterprise face a lot of challenge, even crisis, but at the same time also hide a lot of opportunity, need the enterprise according to the situation oneself excavate. For example, the business model to make some improvements and extension, from the inside to the benefits of innovation. For example, ruixing coffee started to prepare unmanned retail last year, and in February this year, the first ruixing unmanned coffee machine was put into use in Wuhan Liu72 Hospital, meeting the safety and health standards of no contact under special circumstances.

At the same time, ruixing coffee also expanded its business scope, including alcohol disinfectant, antibacterial hand sanitizer and so on. However, the company has been losing money in recent years: 56.37 million yuan in 2017,1.62 billion yuan in 2018 and a net loss of more than 1.7 billion yuan in the first three quarters of 2019. It remains to be seen whether the company will be able to survive the crisis by expanding its business scope.

The VC executives also reminded the investee companies that they need to consider the impact of these measures while addressing their funding issues. For example, the salary will be reduced. Senior executives of VC institutions interviewed by the CAIJING reporter said that while the company is reducing the salary, it may consider making compensation plans, such as changing the salary reduction to a deferred salary. In addition, it can also negotiate with employees and use company options to compensate them, so that employees can work with the company through tough times.

The self-help approach of some small and medium-sized enterprises has been criticized. For example, during the outbreak of the egg Shell apartment, the largest long term rental apartment listed company in the country, the government terminated the contract with the landlord on the grounds of force majeure, which also affected the tenants, some of whom had to pay rent to the egg Shell apartment while facing rent refunds, this caused the company to be in a whirlpool of public opinion. The company's net cash flow of-168 million yuan in the first three quarters of 2019 also highlights the funding crisis it faces.

Metamorphosis: Organic in crisis

The outbreak has had a huge impact on many industries. But there are opportunities in the midst of danger. While most small and medium-sized enterprises (smes) are suffering secondary damage from the epidemic, some of them are heading upstream to face the rare opportunity of business volume outbreak.

"recently, some of the pure-line businesses we've invested in, such as an APP that teaches people how to cook, have more than doubled their traffic since the end of January and February. We also invest in fresh e-commerce companies, such as daily excellent fresh, and so on, to create 'non-contact distribution' way, in everyone is not convenient to go out, not convenient to gather in supermarkets and other confined spaces, business demand explosion. Then there is the rapid growth of demand for telecommuting, and some online office software such as graphite (document co-ordination) is welcoming an influx of customers,"Wu Haiyan told Caijing.

However, the fresh industry business volume, but also encountered some difficulties. One is the impact of the road closures on the supply chain, according to Wu Haiyan. After communication, the logistics of large-scale agricultural products has been resumed. Second, the shortage of distribution staff, the original distribution staff back to the city is not convenient, fresh enterprises to innovate, to accept a number of catering business service staff, to absorb into the warehouse work. In the future, these enterprises also face some challenges, such as how to keep the new customers during the epidemic period after the end of the epidemic, to ensure the continuous growth of business.

Many investors said that the health care industry financing is expected to rise against the trend, the stock market on the collective outbreak of pharmaceutical stocks is a case in point.

The epidemic has exposed our country's deficiencies in the public health system, as well as in medical testing and treatment technologies. In the future, the country will increase its investment in public health and the disease control system, said Wang Bin, a partner at Sun Wukong, to Guide more funds and resources to the various vertical areas of the health care industry, "there will be more and more investment institutions choose to set up a single industry fund, dedicated to the health care industry. ".

In Liu's view, the outbreak will reshape people's behavior and consumption ideas, thus giving birth to new demand for products and services, such as home health. "We are investing in a medical surveillance program that allows patients to take urine tests at home, and the data is sent to a diagnostic center via a smartphone to assist in the diagnosis of chronic kidney disease, which relieves pressure in large hospitals. "

Epidemic hit, "housing economy" , the online form of business has become a new investment outlet. However, the development of artificial intelligence and the application of high-tech are behind the on-line scene, and this track has become the "meat and potatoes" in the eyes of investors.

Yang Shoubin insists that the new smart economy will continue to be heavily invested in the future. According to his judgment, the future enterprises are divided into three categories: first, artificial intelligence enterprises; second, intelligence + Traditional Industries, such as intelligence + consumption, intelligence + Culture and tourism; and third, enterprises eliminated by intelligence, "SARS in 2003 gave birth to the rise of domestic E-COMMERCE, this round of epidemic may accelerate the industry to mobile internet, intelligent Internet upgrade. ".

Peng Cheng focuses on the application of artificial intelligence robots in the fields of medicine and prevention and control, "Some hospitals have given contaminated isolation areas to robots, which are equipped with cameras, microphones and stethoscopes. Doctors operate the robots outside the isolation windows, and the images can be transmitted to remote consultation centers in real time, which helps reduce the occupational exposure of front-line health care workers and avoid the risk of infection. "

In the view of most investors, the epidemic will intensify the reshuffle of various industries, most industries will have a watershed in 2020, the head of high-quality enterprises to further expand market share, bad enterprises may be quickly eliminated.

At the same time, the epidemic has also disrupted the venture capital agencies have raised the tempo. However, a number of VC executives believe that the short-term epidemic will not have a significant impact on investment logic and preferences, but will trigger a new investment trend, companies that have survived both the economic winter and rare epidemics, will be more valuable as an investment.

Yang Shoubin said that after the epidemic ended, will "counter-trend" capital increase small and medium-sized enterprises: "The investment industry must bargain buy. "when markets were crazy, valuations were sky-high and bubbles were big, and the epidemic helped to deflate them, and some valuations hit rock bottom. It was a good opportunity. "

Liu Zehui tends to be more cautious, "projects that are already in the investment decision-making process will proceed normally, while those that are seriously affected by the epidemic may have to be reassessed to see if they have enough core competitiveness to weather the storm, " he said. Still, he stressed, the only company left after the outbreak is a good one.

The outbreak of this capital is shrouded in the winter of the circle of venture capital to add insult to injury. Peng Cheng said that in the future, resources will be more concentrated into three types of capital: First, Redwood, Hillhouse and other top institutions; second, the industrial capital set up by listed companies, such as Batj Internet giant department VC, Xiaomi's Shun Wei capital, and so on; Third, state owned capital.

After 2018, because of the double impact of the new regulation and the economic downturn, the RMB fund-raising faces a structural dilemma. Peng Cheng predicted that in the future it will be more difficult to raise capital, and that investment will slow down and focus more on "management" and "retreat" , "The next step is to guarantee the cash flow of the investee companies, and any exit that is possible will be accelerated. ".

At the same time, in recent years, venture capital institutions "exit difficult" has become increasingly prominent. "At present, the stock of the private equity primary market is close to 9 trillion yuan. The period from 2015 to 2016 is a big explosion in the market. If we follow the traditional '5 + 2' Fund model, these two years are just the time for the central liquidation, " Wang said, iPO is the main exit channel, but the current market capacity is limited, "the new rules lead to an exit period extended by one to two years, time extension, lower yields, the funds can not return late, which further exacerbated the next round of funding. ".

It is foreseeable that in 2020, capital market investment and financing will show a general tightening situation. There is not a winter that can not be crossed, and there is not a spring that can not come. "If you look at the epidemic as a disaster, it doesn't necessarily lead to great enterprises, but we can not rule out that there may be enterprises that are great because of the disaster, " Yang said.
